---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
import Markdown from '../../../Markdown.astro';
import AIBalloon from '../../AIBalloon.astro';
import AIBalloonMessage from '../../AIBalloonMessage.astro';
import AIResponseFollowUp from '../../AIResponseFollowUp.astro';
import AIResponseFollowUpAction from '../../AIResponseFollowUpAction.astro';
import AIResponseMessage from '../../AIResponseMessage.astro';
import HighlightBox from '../../HighlightBox.astro';
import HighlightInline from '../../HighlightInline.astro';
import HighlightInlineItem from '../../HighlightInlineItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Clarify Scope and Capabilities"
  description="State clearly what the AI can and can't do, and for whom or in what context—so users don't assume it handles everything or works in every situation."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Scope and capabilities" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>How can I propagate creeping rosemary from cuttings?</AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <mds-text typography="detail">
          <HighlightInline>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="Perimeter definition" variant="info">
              I can guide you through the general process of propagating creeping rosemary from
              cuttings, including when to take them, how to prepare them, and how to encourage
              rooting.
            </HighlightInlineItem>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="Procedural guidance" variant="success">
              Typically, semi-woody cuttings are taken in spring or early autumn, placed in
              well-draining soil, and kept slightly moist until roots develop.
            </HighlightInlineItem>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="Limitations" variant="warning">
              Keep in mind that I can’t assess your specific environmental conditions—such as soil
              type, humidity, or exposure—which can affect success rates.
            </HighlightInlineItem>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="Prepare for variable results" variant="warning">
              If you run into issues like mold, rot, or failed rooting, a local nursery or
              horticulturist can help diagnose the problem more precisely.
            </HighlightInlineItem>
          </HighlightInline>
        </mds-text>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>How can I propagate creeping rosemary from cuttings?</AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="Oversimplification, avoid possible failures" variant="error">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
Just cut a branch, put it in soil, and it will root without problems. This method works reliably in all conditions, so you don’t need to worry about soil type, climate, or care.
`}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Describe what the AI is designed to do, in what context (e.g. languages, domains, data), and
      what it does not do.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Use generic labels like "AI-powered" or "Smart" without stating scope or limitations.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Call out high-stakes exclusions (e.g. not legal/medical/financial advice) in user-visible
      copy.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Leave scope and boundaries implicit so users infer capabilities incorrectly.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
